                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi all,
<br />

<br />
    There has been alot of talk about charming recently, and I have also been charming with a druid friend lately, and I wanted to make sure I understood the Charm Exp rules. I know they were changed a few months back, but I can't find any info on what those changes were.
<br />

<br />
As I understand it, your pet can take some of the exp, but exactly how much is what I want to know. I think if your pet does all the dmg, he takes 50% of the xp (you get 50%)? And if you do just 1 pt of dmg, and your pet does the rest, the pet gets 33% of the exp (you get 67%), is this correct?
<br />

<br />
Also, my charming strategy goes a little something like this :
<br />
(In PoM with a snarer friend)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Part I - Grab pet</span>
<br />
1) Pull pet with tash
<br />
2) Snarer class friend snares pet
<br />
3) I charm pet
<br />
4) /pet guard here
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Part II - Grab mob</span>
<br />
5) Pull mob to kill with tash
<br />
6) Snarer class snares
<br />
7) I root mob
<br />
<img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /> /pet attack mob
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Part III - Kill both</span>
<br />
9) I haste or slow at right amts so that both pet and mob get to 10% at the same time.....
<br />
10) Invis and root pet (mob should <span style="font-weight: bold">always </span>be rooted)
<br />
11) Nuke both, get exp for both, rinse, repeat
<br />

<br />
My question is this, am I getting full exp for both kills, since I invised before the mob died? Or is the pet still eating part of the exp because it did dmg? Help?
<br />

<br />
ALSO, what about charmed pets in groups, how does this work with a charmed pet doing ALOT of dmg in a group, does it eat part of the groups exp or just part of your exp? If so, how much? and is it relative to dmg? Can't seem to get the answers anywhere.
<br />

<br />
Fading Illusion
<br />
59 Enchanter
<br />
Officer - Force of Valor
