                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have no idea of the grouping rules.
<br />

<br />
However, solo, it is almost as Entharion says.  Do no damage, pet gets 75%, you get 25%.  Do 1 point of damage, pet takes 33%, you get 66%.  That's a big jump for 1 point, I use a ceramic band for that.  In theory, if you do 50% of the damage or more, you will get 100% of the exp, and it is supposed to be on a sliding scale up to there.
<br />

<br />
If your pet is alive, charmed or not, when the mob dies, he gets his share of the experience.  So always, always, kill the pet first.  Personally, I usually keep my pet for several kills, as that is lighter on mana, and I find it easier to buff up a pet to kill a few than it is to judge damage just right so that I don't blow all my mana on several nukes and reroots.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
