                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From the eqlive site (<a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/dev_view.jsp?id=51146" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/dev_view.jsp?id=51146</a>):
<br />

<br />

<br />
if you are <span style="text-decoration: underline">not</span> using Dire Charm then:
<br />
<ul>if group/solo does any damage, pet gets 0% xp
<br />
if group/solo does no damage, pet gets 75% xp</ul>
<br />

<br />
if you are using Dire Charm then:
<br />
<ul>if group/solo does at least 50% damage to mob, pet gets 0% xp
<br />
otherwise pet gets up to 75% xp based on how much damage it did vs. group/solo (sliding scale).</ul>
<br />

<br />
Date of this information is from 2002; but is the latest word I see from SoE on this subject.  Have heard rumors that it changed since then; but no one has been able to supply a link to back it up - so I am sticking with this formula...</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
