                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok Aertea, that officially qualifies as A Good One. 
<br />

<br />
Seems crazy at first, but then you look at particulars- what if charm breaks? Well, then you have a slowed mob chasing you. What if root breaks? Chances are your pet has aggro, so you have no mobs chasing you, re-root. What if charm and root break at the same time? Well, then you have one hasted and one slowed mob  running after you, which is the same thing that happens if you have the hasted one charmed and you are fighting a slowed one.
<br />

<br />
The only thing I would say is I would think this would take a bunch more mana as you end up casting charm a lot. But maybe this is made up for by the exp gain.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
