                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've done some charm killing in PoTactics and used alot of things discussed in this thread. I always try and get a pet that is of the same type of mob that I'm going to be sending it up against (guardian vs. guardian, scout vs. scout etc..) and try my best to widdle them both down to under 10% health. Always keeping the mob being killed rooted, then invising (should have been a DE so I could just /hide) and getting rid of the pet so I can kill them. The old pet will start to walk off, slowly, so I tend to nuke that one down first, then work on the rooted mob. 
<br />

<br />
Neither of them regen too terribly fast, since they are both still have one person on the hate list, me! I believe a PoP mob will regen incredibly fast when no one is left on thier aggro list. Takes me about 20% mana, mostly for the end nukes, to finish off two mobs at once in about 1 minute. Of course, charm breaks, freak adds, and other variables (bards and druids running around the top of the pit mobs in-tow) tend to slow me down, but doing this is pretty safe, just keep scaled wolf and levi on, that way if things go south you can at least jump in the pit and get to the NE ZO.
<br />

<br />
12% AA per two kills, about 20% mana used, pet get no exp because he dies first. Rebuffing, some Arcane rune-ing when hit, all take from the mana pool, this will slow you down, but it is still great solo EXP. Add a snarer and time flies when your having fun  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Aargile Whiteheart, Coercer, Rodcet Nife
<br />

<br />
P.S. - Anyone have a good insta click invis item that you use to get rid of your pets? I hate taking up a spell gem with invis, and potions are ok but 10pp a pop gets old quick too.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
